Boil a #pot of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} for your rice. Wash the @Brown Basmati Rice{175%g} in a #sieve under running water for ~{1%minute}. Rapidly boil the rice on high heat for ~{25%minutes} then drain and put back in the pan. Cover with a #tea towel{} and leave off the heat until the chicken is cooked.

While the rice cooks chop your @British Chicken Thighs{3} into bite sized pieces. Chop the base from the @Pak Choi{2} and chop the bok choy widthways into 4. Very finely chop the @Spring Onion{2} into discs, separating the white and green parts. Slice the @Red Chilli{1/2} in half and very thinly slice widthways.

Peel the @Garlic Clove{1}, crush it under your knife then dice finely. Using the edge of a #spoon peel the skin from the @Ginger{1/2} knob. Now either grate the ginger or dice it super finely.

Mix the garlic, ginger, @Soy Sauce{2%tbsp}, @Caster Sugar{1%tbsp} and @Chinese Rice Vinegar{1}(tablespoon) in a #bowl. Stir in the @Chinese Five Spice{1/2%tsp}. Add as much of the red chilli as you dare. Tip this mixture over the chicken and allow to marinade for as long as your hunger allows.

Heat @oil{1%tbsp} in a #pan on medium-high heat. Once the oil is really hot add in the chicken. Cook for around ~{8%minutes} until you have a nice caramelised outside. The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Every 3 mins put @water{1%tbsp} into the pan and this will 'de-glaze' the pan. That's chef talk for stripping off the little burnt bits that'll give your sauce lots of extra taste! Once the chicken is done you want there to be a little bit of sauce to sink into the rice.

When the chicken is just cooked add in the whites of the spring onions. ~{30%seconds} later add in the bok choi. Stir fry for ~{2%minutes} until the bok choi has wilted.

Serve with your rice and sprinkle over the greens of the spring onions. Bonza!

> Great Australian inspired dish featuring mysterious 5 spices: star anise, cloves, Chinese cinnamon, fennel seeds and Sichuan pepper!